  &lt;Comment&gt;
    &lt;Title&gt;After care not good&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Angie Parrish&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I had excellent care whilst in hospital.  I went in for a total knee replacement in May..  Whilst in hospital I had physio with two people who were both helpful and motivational.  When I came home I had to make 3 appointments, 1 to have my clips removed, my first session of physio and my 6 week consultant appointment which I did.  I attended the physio first which was with a man I had not met before and  I felt like he did not want to help me.  He showed me a couple of exercises to do and recommended I buy some floor pedals which I already had so he told me to use them for 3 minutes or so.  He said there was no point in having much physio unless I wanted to do active things I.e. going to the gym, doing marathons, climbing walls etc and that unless he heard from me in 2 weeks he would discharge me.  I have continued to do exercise at home but unsure whether I am doing these right.  It is a 50 minute journey for me to Rowley Hall so not easy to get to as I cant drive yet so I am going to try and get physio locally on NHS.  The physio just made me feel like I had no right to be there unless i was some sort of athlete.  Disappointed as I am a private paying patient.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
